b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe30016.htm)  [Next](sbe30018.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983862/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 2 (SBE30)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1892], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 51\n\n### K\xc3\x82 _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 5.\n\n1. 1 Now (follow) the ceremonies of the fourth day.\n\n2. 2 Having put wood on the fire, he four times sacrifices expiatory \xc3\x82 _g_ ya oblations with (the formula), 'Agni! Thou art expiation' (MB. I, 4, 1)\xc2\x97\n\n3\\. (And with the same formula), putting instead of Agni, Vayu, _K_ andra, and\nSurya;\n\n4. 4 A fifth oblation (with the names of the four gods) together, changing (in the Mantra the singular) into the plural.\n\n5\\. The remnants of each oblation he should pour into a water-pot.\n\n6. 6 With that (\xc3\x82 _g_ ya) they besmear her body, including her hair and nails, remove (that water and \xc3\x82 _g_ ya by rubbing her), and wash her.\n\n7\\. After three nights have passed, they should cohabit, according to some\n(teachers).\n\n8\\. When she has had her monthly illness and the blood has ceased to flow,\nthat is the time for cohabiting.\n\n9\\. With his right hand he should touch her secret parts with the verse, 'May\nVish _n_ u make thy womb\n\np. 52\n\nready' (MB. I, 4, 6), and with that, 'Give conception, Sinivali' (l.l. 7).\n\n10\\. When those two verses are finished, they cohabit.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[51:1](sbe30017.htm#fr_217) 5, 1. The _K_ aturthikarman.\n\n[51:2](sbe30017.htm#fr_218) 2, 3. Comp. _S_ a\xe1\xb9\x85khayana-G _ri_ hya I, 18, 3;\nKhadira-G _ri_ hya I, 4, 12.\n\n[51:4](sbe30017.htm#fr_219) I.e. instead of praya _s_ _k_ itte (expiation) he\nuses the plural praya _s_ _k_ ittaya _h_ ; and he says, 'you are the\nexpiations of the gods,' &c.\n\n[51:6](sbe30017.htm#fr_220) Khadira-G _ri_ hya I, 4,13. Hrasayitva literally\nmeans, 'having shortened her.' She is 'shortened' by the removing of the\nsubstance with which they have besmeared her (hrasayitva udvartanadina tad\nabhya _\xc3\xb1_ _g_ anam apaniya, says the commentary). Comp. on the technical\nmeaning of hrasana the G _ri_ hya-sa _m_ graha II, 38, 8-10; Khadira-G _ri_\nhya I, 4, 15. 16.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 6](sbe30018.htm)\n\n"